Pools.freeAll() method differs slightly from Pool.freeAll in that it doesn't check whether the array objects are null, thus resulting in a possible NPE. 

The code in Pools is:

``` java
for (int i = 0, n = objects.size; i < n; i++) {
    Object object = objects.get(i);
    ReflectionPool pool = typePools.get(object.getClass());
```

The corresponding code in Pool.freeAll is:

``` java
for (int i = 0; i < objects.size; i++) {
    T object = objects.get(i);
    if (object == null) continue;
```

A similar null check in Pools would do the trick.
